\f1\b0\fs38 \cf2 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F
\f0\b\fs60 \

\f1\b0\fs38 For the crust: In a food processor, combine the confectioners' sugar, flour, and butter, and process until the mixture forms a ball. With your fingers, press the dough into mini tart pans with a removable bottom, taking care to push the crust into the indentations in the sides. Pat until the crust is even. Bake for 5 to 7 minutes, until very lightly browned. Set aside to cool.
\f0\b\fs50 \

\f1\b0\fs40 To make lemon curd:\
Combine all of the ingredients, except butter, and whip over a double boiler.  Whisk the mixture until thickened.  Strain the curd into a mixing bowl and mix with paddle to cool.\
Once the mixture is 140 degrees F add the butter and mix until cool. Store refrigerated, well wrapped, until ready to use.\
To make meringue:\
In a double broiler heat the egg whites and sugar until all the graininess of the sugar has dissolved.  Add cream of tartar.  Whip the mixture until cooled and thickened into a shiny meringue, about 4 to 7 minutes.\
